eceased","1182–Male":"1182–Deceased","1214–1314":"1214–1314","1150–Male":"1150–Deceased","1150–1264":"1150–1264","1314":"1314","1214":"1214","1264":"1264","1186":"1186","liv 1625":"1625","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","Orwey, Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Anstell, Devon., Eng.":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Devon, Eng.":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Raleigh, Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Raleigh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Raleigh (House) in Pilton (Devon), recorded as <i>Radeleia</i> in 1086 and <i>Rawlegh</i> in 1535. The placename probably derives from Old English <i>rǣge</i> ‘roe deer’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: variant of   Riley  .","History: The English explorer Sir Walter Raleigh (1554–1618) was born in Hayes Barton, Devon, into a family of Devon gentry. He was related to most of the West Country's important families, including that of Sir Francis Drake. His half-brother was the explorer Sir Humphrey Gilbert. In 1578 Raleigh was granted a patent to explore and colonize “unknown lands” in America. In the 1580s he was granted extensive estates in Munster (Ireland), in reward for his suppression of the Desmond Rebellions."],"variants":[{"name":"Raley","meanings":["English: variant of   Raleigh  ."]},{"name":"Rawleigh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Orlo.","English: variant of   Raleigh  , reflecting a common pronunciation."]},{"name":"Riley","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name chiefly from High Ryley in Accrington (Lancashire) and Riley in Kirkburton, which was in the manor of Wakefield (Yorkshire). In some cases the name may derive from Riley Farm in Eyam (Derbyshire), Royley in Royton (Lancashire), or Rylah in Scarcliffe (Derbyshire). The placenames all come from Old English <i>rȳge</i> ‘rye’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>. This is the name of a chieftain family in Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b> or   Rahilly  . See   O'Reilly  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes de Raleigh was born in 1186, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir John de Raleigh, was 11183 and her mother, Elizabeth Bamville, was 11183. She had at least 1 son with John Orway. She died in Somme, Picardie, France."},"et":{"1186–":"1186–Surnud","1186–Female":"1186–Surnud","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","1214–1314":"1214–1314","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1150–1264":"1150–1264","1314":"1314","1214":"1214","1264":"1264","1186":"1186","liv 1625":"1625","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Orwey, Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Anstell, Devon., Eng.":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, Eng.":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Raleigh, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1186–":"1186–Kuollut","1186–Female":"1186–Kuollut","1182–Male":"1182–Kuollut","1214–1314":"1214–1314","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1150–1264":"1150–1264","1314":"1314","1214":"1214","1264":"1264","1186":"1186","liv 1625":"1625","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Orwey, Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Anstell, Devon., Eng.":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, Eng.":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Raleigh, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1186–":"1186–Décédée","1186–Female":"1186–Décédée","1182–Male":"1182–Décédé","1214–1314":"1214–1314","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1150–1264":"1150–1264","1314":"1314","1214":"1214","1264":"1264","1186":"1186","liv 1625":"1625","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","Orwey, Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Anstell, Devon., Eng.":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, Eng.":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Raleigh, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-U